fields.physical_description:
contained in a wooden cigar box together with a paper booklet of rules; scoring card and home made score card
144 unvarnished wooden tiles, each with hand drawn letter/number and design arranged in sets of four; sets are as follows
1-4  pictogram in green to represent the Green Dragon, letter F
5-8  blank to represent the White Dragon, letter P in black
9-12  pictogram in red to represent the Red Dragon, letter C
13-16  pictogram in black to represent the East Wind, letter E
17-20  pictogram in black to represent the South Wind, letter S
21-24  pictogram in black to represent the West Wind, letter W
25-28  pictogram in black to represent the North Wind, letter N
29-32  decorated circle in red, black and green to represent 1 in the Circles suit, number 1 within
33-36  two sets of concentric circles in green to represent 2 in the Circles suit, with the number 2
37-40  three sets of concentric circles in black to represent 3 in the Circles suit, with the  number 3
41-44  four sets of concentric circles in red to represent 4 in the Circles suit, with the number 4
45-48  five sets of concentric circles in red to represent 5 in the Circles suit, with the number 5
49-52  six sets of concentric circles in black to represent 6 in the Circles suit, with the number 6
53-56  seven sets of concentric circles in green to represent 7 in the Circles suit, with the number 7
57-60  eight sets of concentric circles in red to represent 8 in the Circles suit, with the number 8
61-64  nine sets of concentric circles (three in red, three in black, three in green) to represent 9 in the Circles suit, with the number 9
65-68  number 1 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 1 in the Characters suit
69-72 number 2 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 2 in the Characters suit
73-76  number 3 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 3 in the Characters suit
77-80  number 4 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 4 in the Characters suit
81-84  number 5 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 5 in the Characters suit
85-88  number 6 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 6 in the Characters suit
89-92  number 7 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 7 in the Characters suit
93-96  number 8 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 8 in the Characters suit
97-100  number 9 with two pictograms (one in red, one in black) to represent 9 in the Characters suit
101-104  number 1 with stylized bird in black and green to represent 1 in the Bamboo suit
105-108   number 2 with two pieces of bamboo in green to represent 2 in the Bamboo suit
109-112   number 3 with three pieces of bamboo in red to represent 3 in the Bamboo suit
113-116   number 4 with four pieces of bamboo in black to represent 4 in the Bamboo suit
117-120   number 5 with five pieces of bamboo in green to represent 5 in the Bamboo suit
121-124   number 6 with two pieces of bamboo in black to represent 6 in the Bamboo suit
125-128   number 7 with seven pieces of bamboo in green to represent 7 in the Bamboo suit
129-132   number 8 with eight pieces of bamboo in red to represent 8 in the Bamboo suit
133-136   number 9 with nine pieces of bamboo (three in red, three in black, three in green) to represent 9 in the Bamboo suit
137  number 1 with stylized flowers to represent 1 in the Flowers suit
138  number 2 with stylized flowers to represent 2 in the Flowers suit
139 number 3 with stylized flowers to represent 3 in the Flowers suit
140 number 4 with stylized flowers to represent 4 in the Flowers suit
141 number 1 to represent 1 in the Seasons suit
142 number 2 to represent 2 in the Seasons suit
143 number 3 to represent 3 in the Seasons suit
144 number 4 to represent 4 in the Seasons suit
[booklet] booklet of rules, printed paper
[leaflet] method of scoring leaflet, printed card
[sheets (information artifacts)] hand made scoring sheets
